uid4nps

Class UseridNpsDtsParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • uid4nps.UseridNpsDtsParser

  • public class UseridNpsDtsParser
extends java.lang.Object
    Use the IMIParser(java.lang.String) method for each NPS DTS-formated element (Radius Log entries) IMIParser(java.lang.String) will return TRUE is the element in compliant (Acc-Start with UserName and FramedIP) Element values available after parsing accessing the elementData field with keys "User-Name", "Framed-IP-Address" and "NAS-Identifier"

    • Method Detail

      • IMIParser

        public java.lang.Boolean IMIParser(java.lang.String element)
                            throws java.io.IOException
        This method will discard any non useful DTS message. We'll only keep these one that satisfy:
        • Matches the user-provided regular expression in the in the configuration file userid4nps.includePattern
        • Have an "Acct-Status-Type" element node
        • The "Acct-Status-Type" element node has values "1" (start) or "2" (stop) or "3" (interim)
        • Have an "User-Name" element node
        • Have a "Framed-IP-Address"element node
        In case the "User-Name" value doesn't include a domain name we'll use the one at defaultDomain
        Parameters:
        element - The DTS Compliant NPS log formated entry to be parsed
        Returns:
        TRUE if we've been able to parse the entry so caller knows there is valid data available at elementData
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
